cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with replication in parallel systems and proposes a novel replication policy to improve the stability region of fork-join queueing systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses reducing latencies in parallel systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a theoretical framework to compute tight bounds on the distribution of response times in general replication systems. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper discusses minimizing response time quantiles and improving the stability region of queueing systems. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with multiagent systems, but the concept of replication can be applied in such systems.
